### HTTP Request

`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/slider`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                                  |
|-------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| did         | false    | Device ID. You get it from `init` method in SDK.             |
| email       | false    | User's email                                                 |
| phone       | false    | User's phone                                                 |
| external_id | false    | User's ID from your database                                 |
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                                 |
| code        | true     | Slider unique code                                           |
| tags        | false    | Banner tags to filter banners (comma-separated list of tags) |


### API response

Main object structure:

| Name       | Type     | Description              |
|:-----------|:---------|:-------------------------|
| properties | object   | Slider properties object |
| slides     | banner[] | List of banners          |


Structure of `properties` object:

| Name   | Type    | Description             |
|:-------|:--------|:------------------------|
| code   | string  | Slider's unique code    |
| width  | integer | Banner width in pixels  |
| height | integer | Banner height in pixels |

Structure of `banner` element:

| Name             | Type   | Description                        |
|:-----------------|:-------|:-----------------------------------|
| image_url        | string | Image URL                          |
| url              | string | Destination URL                    |
| deeplink_ios     | string | Deeplink for iOS                   |
| deeplink_android | string | Deeplink for Android               |
| content_type     | string | Content type (reserved property)   |
| content          | text   | Banner content (reserved property) |
| html             | html   | Banner content (HTML)              |

